author: Xyla Foxlin
description:
Two years ago, I built a “bulletproof” ball gown… that didn’t fit me. Turns out, wrapping yourself in duct tape and filling it with foam isn’t the most accurate way to make a mannequin. So this time, I brought in Hollywood special-effects pros to literally cast my entire body in plaster to make “Xyla-Foam 2.0.” It’s messy, weirdly scientific, and mildly horrifying—but also kind of beautiful.

Watch the full video to see how we cloned me in foam (and what I plan to build next).
